THE FLAG
-----------------------------------------------------------

picoCTF{307019}


-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

Assembly is just C in disguise. Once you recognize movl, add, cmp, and jl you
can reconstruct what any program does without ever seeing the source code.

The eax register holds the return value of a function. Whatever is in eax when
ret executes is the answer the function gives back.

GDB is not just for debugging crashes. It is a powerful tool for understanding
how any compiled program works from the inside.

Converting hex to decimal with p/d saves time and avoids errors. Always let the
tool do the arithmetic when possible.
